Hawkins accident prevention program includes:

1. Procedures and training for handling chemicals during shipping and storage;

2. Ensure vendor provides DOT approved cylinders;

3. Provide employees with equipment to safely move chemicals during storage and transportation;

4. Adhere to OSHA workplace regulations;

5. Follow Chlorine Institute standards.



5-year Accident History:  There has not been an accident involving chlorine at this facility in the last 5 years.



Emergency Response:  In the event of a maintenance issue with chlorine equipment/rail car, employees are trained on how to detect the source of the issue and take appropriate action such as closing or tightening a valve.  If a larger accident should occur, this facility has a trained hazmat team and proper equipment (SCBA and C-kits) on-site to respond.  This facility also has a good working relationship with the local emergency planning committee and hazardous material responders (St. Clair Special Emergency Association) as well as the local volunteer Fire Department.



Planned Changes:  While Hawkins desires to continually improve safety, there are no specific changes planned other than to continue compliance with industry standards and government regulations and our own commitment to "Think Safe! Be Safe!"
